Project 2 to Project 3 Improvement
Overview

Project 3, RecoveryPilot, builds on the academic planning direction from Project 2, DeadlinePilot, but changes the architecture to better meet the course goals around MCP tools, agentic behavior, autonomous decision-making, evaluation, and production quality.

The main Project 2 feedback was that the system worked, but most of the named agents were deterministic TypeScript functions. The LLM was added as a reviewer, but the core planning decision was still largely hardcoded.

RecoveryPilot addresses this by making the LLM responsible for the final recovery strategy decision after receiving structured output from a custom MCP-style tool.

Comparison Table
Area	Project 2: DeadlinePilot	Project 3: RecoveryPilot Improvement
AI role	LLM acted mainly as a reviewer after deterministic planning logic	LLM chooses the final recovery strategy mode
