Production quality	Good class demo UI	Draft moves toward a more realistic student recovery assistant
Main Improvement

The biggest improvement is that Project 3 makes the AI decision visible and testable.

In Project 2, a grader could reasonably say the system was mostly deterministic. In Project 3, the app shows:

the custom tool output
the LLM strategy decision
the model’s reasoning
the deterministic baseline comparison

This makes the agentic behavior clearer.

Why This Is More Agentic

RecoveryPilot does not simply sort tasks by due date. It gives the model structured workload information and asks it to select a strategy.

The model can decide that the student needs:

a normal schedule
a recovery plan
a triage plan
an overload warning

This is more agentic than the previous version because the LLM is responsible for selecting the planning mode.

Draft Limitations

This draft still needs final polish before the final submission. The current app includes a lot of class/project evidence directly in the UI. That is helpful for grading, but the final version should make the main interface more student-facing and move technical evidence into a separate section.

The final version should also improve:

workload calculation clarity
risk flag detection
scheduling guardrails
date/time formatting
product polish
